h3. Problem

When using Jira default fields as required on Portfolio while creating issues on Portfolio, the commit does not work as expected but the issue is created.

h3. Steps to reproduce

# Configure the field configuration of the project where the issue is going to be created to have a Jira Default Field as required (examples: Description, Component, Fix Version, etc.);
# Create an issue on the Portfolio that uses this field configuration;
# Proceed with the commit changes process and fill the required fields as usual;
# The following error occurs: {color:red}An issue cannot be updated as required fields are missing. Please define a value or mark the field as optional to resolve the problem.{color}

h3. Expected Results

The commit should happen normally.

h3. Actual Results

The issue is created but not committed.

h3. Workaround

Make default Jira field as optional in order to commit the changes in the plan.

